headline: CoStar Group (CSGP): Assessing Valuation as Shares Decline 12% This Month
summary: CoStar Group (CSGP) shares have turned lower recently, giving up 12% over the past month. Despite this, the company’s strong annual revenue growth and improving net income raise questions about its long-term prospects for patient investors. See our latest analysis for CoStar Group. While CoStar Group’s 1-year total shareholder return has slipped into negative territory, its share price performance year-to-date is still in positive territory.
